      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>grated beetroot </strong>to a medium sized pot with the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> tamarind paste</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Season with<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and bring to a boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook for 10-15 min, stirring frequently, or until thickened to a jam-like consistency – this is your <strong>beetroot chutney</strong></p>",
