    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, drain the <strong>soaked lentils</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>drained lentils </strong>to a <strong>food processor</strong> with 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and the <strong>remaining curry powder</strong> and blitz until smooth</p><p>Once smooth, transfer the <strong>lentil mixture</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half</strong> the<strong> chopped coriander</strong> and <strong>nigella seeds </strong>and mix until fully combined – this is your <strong>batter</strong></p>",
